        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "By default Zend_Controller_Request_Http::getClientIp() checks for X-Forwarded-For that leads to easy IP spoofing. This is a very dangerous default since method can be used for IP-based authorization:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nif(in_array(getClientIp(), $allowedAddresses))\r\n{\r\n  echo 'I am admin! Yay!';\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIf you're not sure if it's good to break backwards compatibility in order to prevent it and if it's better just to mention it somewhere in the documentation, check these:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/blog\/1068-public-key-security-vulnerability-and-mitigation\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/blog\/1069-responsible-disclosure-policy"
        },
